con = sqlite3.connect(r"../laliga.sqlite")
# Change date format (2029 -> 1929)
df = pd.read_sql_query("SELECT * FROM Matches", con)

# Data formatting:
# We split the "date" column into the corresponding columns, and specify the correct formatting.
# This way we avoid the year 29 or higher to be mistaken by 2029 (error with to_datetime function).
df[["month", "day", "year"]] = df["date"].str.split("/", 2, expand = True)
df["year"] = df["year"].apply(lambda x: f"19{x}" if int(x) >= 23 else f"20{x}")
df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df[['day', 'month', 'year']]).dt.strftime('%d/%m/%Y') 

# We also change the formatting of the time to be in 24h format
df['time'] = df['time'].apply(lambda x: datetime.strftime(datetime.strptime(x, "%I:%M %p"), "%H:%M") if type(x) == str else x)

df[["home_goals", "away_goals"]] = df["score"].str.split(":", expand=True).astype(float)
df2=df.dropna(subset = "score")
df2["goal diff"] = (df2["home_goals"]  - df2["away_goals"])
df2["results"] = np.where(df2["goal diff"] > 0, "1", np.where(df2["goal diff"] < 0, "2", "X"))
df2['home_win'] = df['home_goals'] > df['away_goals']

def parse_seasons(value):
    if value == "all":
        return "all"
    seasons = []
    for chunk in value.split(","):
        if ":" in chunk:
            try:
                start, end = map(int, chunk.split(":"))
                assert start < end
            except Exception:
                print("error")
            for i in range(start, end):
                seasons.append(f"{i}-{i+1}")
        else:
            try:
                start, end = map(int, chunk.split("-"))
                assert start == end - 1
            except Exception:
                print("error")
            seasons.append(chunk)
    return seasons
In [ ]:
def avg_ranking_goals(team, df, gen_dic, res_dic):
    ranking = []
    net_goals = []
    seasons = df["season"].unique()
    for season in seasons:
        try:
            ranking.append(gen_dic["seasonal_data"][season][team][0])
        except KeyError:
            pass
        try:
            net_goals.append(gen_dic["seasonal_data"][season][team][1])
        except KeyError:
            pass
    avg_ranking = round(np.average(ranking), 3)
    avg_net_goals = round(np.average(net_goals), 3)
    res_dic[team] = [avg_ranking, avg_net_goals]

#TRAINIG SEASONS 30 YRS
train_seasons = parse_seasons("1990:2020")
train_df_30 = df2[df2["season"].isin(train_seasons)]

dic_import_data = {}
with open("../feature_data.json", "r") as infile:
    dic_import_data = json.load(infile)

dic_feature_data = {}

train_df_30["rank_diff"] = 0
train_df_30["goal_diff"] = 0

for index, row in train_df_30.iterrows():
    home_team = row["home_team"]
    away_team = row["away_team"]
    if home_team not in dic_feature_data:
        avg_ranking_goals(home_team, train_df_30, dic_import_data, dic_feature_data)
    if away_team not in dic_feature_data:
        avg_ranking_goals(away_team, train_df_30, dic_import_data, dic_feature_data)
    train_df_30.loc[row.name, "rank_diff"] = dic_feature_data[home_team][0] - dic_feature_data[away_team][0]
    train_df_30.loc[row.name, "goal_diff"] = dic_feature_data[home_team][1] - dic_feature_data[away_team][1]
    train_df_30.loc[row.name, "home_team"] = dic_import_data["teams_codif"][home_team]
    train_df_30.loc[row.name, "away_team"] = dic_import_data["teams_codif"][away_team]

with open("train_features.json", "w") as outfile:
    json.dump(dic_feature_data, outfile)

Two databases have been created covering different seasons for both training and testing, so that we can analyse the results and the accuracy of the predictions. The training databases have been created with a substantial difference in data, in the first case we have 30 years of match results while in the second case only 5 years. In the case of the seasons chosen for testing, we have chosen the season immediately following the last season for which we have data, and one that happens within 10 years.

4 different predictions will be made by combining these databases.

#CASE 1
cmap_light = ListedColormap(["orange", "cyan", "cornflowerblue"])
cmap_bold = [ "darkblue", "darkorange", "c"]

n_neighbors = 10
weights = "uniform"
clf = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors, weights=weights, algorithm="ball_tree")
clf.fit(x_train_reduced_1, y_train_reduced_1)

_, ax = plt.subplots()
DecisionBoundaryDisplay.from_estimator(
    clf,
    x_train_reduced_1,
    cmap=cmap_light,
    ax=ax,
    response_method="predict",

#CASE 1: WEIGHT UNIFORM
def Accuracy_table(Weight):
    
    acc_df = accuracy_df[accuracy_df.Weight == Weight]
    
    table = pd.crosstab(accuracy_df.Algorithm, accuracy_df.Neighbors, rownames=['Algorithms'], colnames=['Number of neighbors'], values=accuracy_df.Accuracy, aggfunc='first')
    
    return table
